var map = function(arr, fn) {
    let result = [];

    for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
        result[i] = fn(arr[i], i);
    }

    return result;
};



Problem-
Given:
arr → integer array
fn → function

Return a new array:

result[i] = fn(arr[i], i)
Constraint: Do not use built-in Array.map
Logic
Create an empty array result
Loop through arr
For each index i:
Apply function → fn(arr[i], i)
Store result in new array
